high.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[138,1185,1046,1232]" pageId="18" pageNumber="245">Stem strongly polysiphonic; only distalmost branches monosiphonic. Stems branched more or less irregularly in one plane. Some basal branches becoming lower-order stems; branches up to five-order, sometimes anastomosing.</paragraph>
